## Install Android NDK

Download Android NDK from the [Android developer site](https://developer.android.com/ndk/downloads).

The cross-compiler you need is `armv7a-linux-androideabi21-clang`. On Windows it is a `.cmd` file located inside the NDK installation:

```
C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\ndk\<version>\
  toolchains\llvm\prebuilt\windows-x86_64\bin\
  armv7a-linux-androideabi21-clang.cmd
```

On Linux it is at:

```
~/Android/Sdk/ndk/<version>/toolchains/llvm/prebuilt/linux-x86_64/bin/armv7a-linux-androideabi21-clang
```

Verify the compiler works:

```bash { line_numbers = "true" }
armv7a-linux-androideabi21-clang --version
```

Expected output:

```output
Android (clang version 17.x.x)
Target: armv7a-unknown-linux-android21
```

## Create the benchmark file

Create a file named `neon_bench.c`. The full source code is available at [github.com/poojithdevan4D/QuantEdge](https://github.com/poojithdevan4D/QuantEdge).

## Compile for armeabi-v7a

```bash { line_numbers = "true" }
armv7a-linux-androideabi21-clang \
  -O2 \
  -mfpu=neon \
  -mfloat-abi=softfp \
  -o neon_bench_arm \
  neon_bench.c \
  -lm
```

Each flag serves a specific purpose:

| Flag | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `-O2` | Enable optimization — compiler vectorizes independent operations |
| `-mfpu=neon` | Enable NEON hardware on target, required to use `arm_neon.h` intrinsics |
| `-mfloat-abi=softfp` | Android armeabi-v7a ABI — required or the binary crashes on launch |
| `-lm` | Link math library — provides `expf()` |

## Deploy to device via ADB

Push the binary to the device and run it:

```bash { line_numbers = "true" }
adb push neon_bench_arm /data/local/tmp/neon_bench_arm
adb shell chmod 777 /data/local/tmp/neon_bench_arm
adb shell /data/local/tmp/neon_bench_arm
```

{{% notice Note %}}
Use `/data/local/tmp/` and not `/sdcard/`. The sdcard partition is mounted `noexec` on Android — binaries cannot run from it.
{{% /notice %}}
